	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>anyone dumped Cybernoid?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />With 'dumped', I wish I meant throwing it into a dumpster for being horribly hard, but I don't. The reason I ask is because the ROM from GoodNES won't work in an emulator if it inits RAM with $FF instead of $00, known to some over here. If you did dump it, and it differs from the GoodNES one, could you post an IPS file that shows the changes between the hopefully faulty ROM and yours?
<br />
<br />If anyone wants to be able to play the game in all emulators, here's a hack that makes it work: iNES file offset $8002: change {00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 03 80 00 80} to {a9 00 8d fb 05 4c 00 80 03 80 f2 ff}, this writes $00 to RAM location $5FB at startup.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


